    description: "Some Botox providers charge by the unit ($12–$20 per unit); others charge a flat rate per area ($200–$400 per area). Both structures can produce the same treatment — but they create very different financial dynamics. Understanding the difference prevents overpaying and helps you evaluate whether you're getting a fair deal.",
    publishedDate: "2026-05-16",
    readTime: "6 min read",
